Phrenetick, (
   〈◊〉
) possessed with a Phrensie, i. a certain kind of madnesse, arising from an inflammation of the membranes of the brain.

Tybur, a City not far from Rome, built as some say by Catillus the Arcadian the Admiral of Euander; 
   •
thers by Tyburtus the grandchild of Amphiaraus: it is now called Tivoli.
